<br>
Kurk the Fisherman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ujareckthundershot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jareck Thundershot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/01 12:19:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I just might</span><hr size=1> There are a few aspects of this game that I really like...<br>
<br>
PvP-  I like how this is set up, looks very interesting.  One of the best things IMO is that there is no /tell communication between opposing realms.  Only communication between them is done in say from what I understand.  This is a HUGE improvement over EQ's &lt;laugh&gt; PvP.  Also, I like how you may only have characters in one realm per server.  This prevents the spy factor of EQ PvP.<br>
<br>
Also, I like how they are proposing realm points, so that those who defend their realm and invade the other realms can gain enough points to eventually gain titles and become lords, knights, etc. of their realm.<br>
<br>
Quests- this is probably the thing I look forward to most.  The most complicated part of their gaming system (according to reports) is their quest engine, which give out parts of the quest sequentially, but never in the same order, and sometimes giving out different items.  These quests seem like they'll be a lot of fun and will prevent people from camping item a for 3 days then turning in the items to recieve ph4t l33wt z for camping said items.  You will actually have to do the quest all the way through and not just give the final item.<br>
<br>
This game has great potential, although SWG is still on the top of my list.<br>
<br>
Jareck Thundershot<br>
48th Season Ranger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ubalrak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balrak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/01 1:22:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Beta info here</span><hr size=1> Well this is what I know from people I know in RL who are beta testing it out. They said it's decent, now this was umm a good month or so ago. Graphics he said were decent, spells were nice, he did make mention about armor and such being VERY expensive to purchase so don't look forward to running around in full plate in night one.  :)<br>
<br>
I know I am going to give it a shot, I just like the time period it takes place in, so it ought to be interesting to say the least. I've gotten away from PvP on EQ but I sure miss the PvP days of UO when I did pvp. I think it's time to go back to PvP.Not to mention I've been following the production of this game now for well over a year so I do look forward to it's release.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, if I see these guys I will ask them how it's looking and give you a more recent update. Like I said I heard it wasn't bad, it's decent. But alot can change in a month in a game production.<br>
<br>
Balrak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueuthanasiawarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euth Anasia Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/01 1:42:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How many people are going to try camelot?</span><hr size=1> Im getting SO tired of the Dragon Type games myself.  Anarchy online, Star Wars etc etc will be my next whirl(even though they are a long time coming).  I liked EQ because there was really no way around working hard -vs- reward.  There is noone over level 50 that just &quot;spent a few hours&quot; at the game.  To me, that is ver cool.  I played Asherons Call and UO.  In both those (especially UO), you could make a god character in 2-3 ays.  Hell, you could make a God character in UO with EZ Macro overnight.  Comparitively to other Online RPG's, EQ is bug free in my opinion.  I remember playing for over an hour in Ultima Online and then getting time warped back 2 hours or so.  That was 2 hours of work down the drain.  This literally happened over 2-300 times.  Anyway, heh, I want something new and weill pay good for it :)   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ufflewddurfflam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fflewddur Fflam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/01 5:30:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> I'll be playing it for sure.  And I will not be playing Shadowbane.  PvP, blech.<br>
